Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.92,0:01:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P.i.n.e.a.p.p.l.e.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.77,0:01:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of chance. Anybody can win one out of ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.02,0:01:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scissors, paper, rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.25,0:01:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I win again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.38,0:02:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're late. What's holding them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.05,0:02:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scissors, p..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.36,0:02:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you said your eye sight went down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.85,0:02:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fine, let's do it with telepathy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}OK, I'll win three in a row this time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.40,0:02:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Scissors, paper, ...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.44,0:02:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll phone Tomomi's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.65,0:02:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get going. See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, I wanna see nude, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.82,0:02:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P.i.n. e.a.p. p.l.e... What about noodle?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.63,0:02:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.35,0:02:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're late. What took you so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.28,0:02:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I was play with Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.40,0:02:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do scissors paper rock, win with paper, you make steps saying "pineapple."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.26,0:02:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most kids stop playing that after elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.58,0:02:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's pretty fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.23,0:02:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And where's Mikage?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mikage, Mikage, I'm already at the art museum.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.99,0:03:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurashige-sempai's awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he sent in a sketch from England, and that got selected...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.45,0:03:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the prefectural high school art contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.41,0:03:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this way, Noda! There's a nude painting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tomomi, where are you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.10,0:03:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Over here. Come on. Sempai's sketches are great.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.29,0:04:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, there you are. Sempai's drawings are over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you sense out of this painting, Yamagishi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say this curvature of bust is quite artistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.87,0:04:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.10,0:05:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wonderful, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sempai's blending into London.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.53,0:05:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like he might have forgotten about us and became Londoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.35,0:05:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way. Look. This one looks like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.52,0:05:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sempai...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.13,0:05:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, weren't sempai's drawings great?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's him. How could it be lousy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.92,0:05:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A raccoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.64,0:05:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.77,0:05:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going further away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.04,0:05:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's moving again? To Egypt?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.38,0:05:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:05:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got Kageura's exam tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.39,0:06:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.28,0:06:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you lucky? You don't have to panic over exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.03,0:06:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.11,0:07:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How come you came to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.74,0:07:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage! Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.25,0:07:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, you'll be late again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.70,0:07:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she lucky sleeping sound and happy on the day of chem exam?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had dream that Kageura-sensei just keep on laughing at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.26,0:07:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The worst nightmare I've ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:08:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream? Was it a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.37,0:08:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the unicorn's scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may begin. I have gathered assortment of impossible questions bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.21,0:08:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,enough to make you see nightmares for a next week or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.31,0:08:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be done with this easy stuff real quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.11,0:08:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's play together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.05,0:08:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With such a dreamy face, I am bound to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:08:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you finished already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.47,0:08:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.43,0:09:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you're twelve minutes faster than my estimate. Was it that easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.81,0:09:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.19,0:09:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't disturb others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.02,0:09:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sempai used to watch sea from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.45,0:09:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? You can see the ocean really well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about sempai, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.44,0:09:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His picture is in the same art museum as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.31,0:09:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who drew the pictures of London.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.60,0:10:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tickle me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.78,0:10:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.01,0:10:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe it. Even scientist wouldn't be able to get those questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.08,0:10:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least if he could ask us what's covered in text book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.49,0:10:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell would study about undiscovered elements on the night side of the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.76,0:10:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long has she been asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.88,0:10:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sempai used to hang around here, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,London's too far away, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I go abroad, would you remember about me when you stand on the race track?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.87,0:11:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way, right? I'm gonna blow the exam anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.51,0:11:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with English its just about the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.02,0:11:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how can you go study abroad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say Mikage, wanna have chips?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.06,0:12:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.89,0:12:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take me to London.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.84,0:13:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who are you talking to?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take me to sempai.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mikage! Mikage!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you asleep?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mikage...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pretty. It's like stars forming a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.81,0:15:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moonlight is the same wherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.95,0:15:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same wherever I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:16:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, what does she usually eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.30,0:16:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.20,0:16:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're up? Why were you wandering around in midnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.88,0:16:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had me worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.34,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.78,0:16:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.10,0:16:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was playing with the unicorn. I'll show him to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.14,0:16:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, oxygen react with most of other elements to form an oxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.44,0:16:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And oxides are classified into...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.19,0:16:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,oxides, peroxides and superoxides. {I'm aware this is not what he is saying but the 2nd half of the sentence was missing, so I tried to fill in something fitting}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.93,0:16:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was heck of a news. Of all people Mikage blew the chem exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.38,0:16:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.20,0:16:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been acting weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.94,0:16:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.26,0:16:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She muttered something about unicorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.32,0:17:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There. Unicorn: one of most popular imaginary beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.30,0:17:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It supposedly weave human dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.94,0:17:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weave dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.89,0:17:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it draws people into dream word.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.63,0:18:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you came again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.67,0:18:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a real unicorn...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.01,0:18:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi. Tomomi, you can see him too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.37,0:18:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking of taking you to a ride with him even if I have to drag you out of bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, let's fly with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.70,0:18:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take us to London!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.00,0:19:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call Noda-kun over, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.29,0:19:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scissors, paper, rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.62,0:19:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.81,0:19:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, you better win or we'll leave you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.41,0:19:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scissors, paper, rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mikage lose again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.66,0:19:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Don't leave me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.71,0:19:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, here we go. Scissors, paper, rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.34,0:20:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Mikage-kun win!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.14,0:20:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, come over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With grand special unicorn, I want to see sempai real badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you caught up with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.31,0:20:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.83,0:20:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scissors, paper, rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.39,0:20:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:21:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moonlight is the same wherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.81,0:21:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,London, or Yokohama, it's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.66,0:21:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing will change, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.30,0:21:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.71,0:21:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saw dream about sempai?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.37,0:21:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.10,0:21:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too. All of us were playing scissors, paper, rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.53,0:21:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the moon pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.56,0:21:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.66,0:21:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miracle Girls here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh god. A dinosaur appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.49,0:21:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dinosaur?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.00,0:21:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It popped out of a fossil suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.58,0:21:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could that be a ghost of a dinosaur?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.29,0:22:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next on Miracle Girls:\N"Voice Calling into Fog"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.12,0:22:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be looking for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.88,0:22:09.30,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.43,0:22:12.60,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,there has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.52,0:22:15.93,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we had a fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.19,0:22:19.15,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:35.79,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days when kindness is so close
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:39.08,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,, that you can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.38,0:22:52.60,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we know it better than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:59.02,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,When we can't say "I'm sorry,"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.10,0:23:06.07,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,we send out feelings through the little fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.82,0:23:12.83,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Going over the tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:15.74,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,we want to be honest to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.04,0:23:21.17,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause the sky deserves a rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:24.21,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:27.67,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,there has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.55,0:23:30.76,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Two of us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:34.14,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,are better than one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.15,0:22:25.65,credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Ending Song\N"There has to be Both of Us"\N("Futarijanakya Dame Nano")\NBy Dio
